sequenceDiagram
    participant DB_FEED as DataBento Feed
    participant FH as feed-health.ts
    participant BB as bar-builder.ts
    participant TV as TradingView M-16
    participant WH as Webhook Receiver
    participant PB as processBar()
    participant NOTIF as Owner Notification
    participant DASH as Dashboard

    Note over DB_FEED,DASH: Normal operation — DataBento primary

    DB_FEED->>FH: Messages arriving normally
    FH->>DASH: SSE: feed_health { state: CONNECTED }

    Note over DB_FEED: --- DataBento disconnects ---

    DB_FEED--xFH: TCP socket closed
    FH->>FH: Transition: CONNECTED → RECONNECTING
    FH->>NOTIF: "DataBento disconnected"
    FH->>DASH: SSE: feed_health { state: RECONNECTING }

    loop Reconnection attempts (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s...)
        FH->>DB_FEED: Reconnect attempt
        DB_FEED--xFH: Connection refused
    end

    Note over FH: After 3 failed attempts

    FH->>FH: Transition: RECONNECTING → FALLBACK_ACTIVE
    FH->>BB: Suspend processBar() trigger
    FH->>WH: Activate M-16 as primary
    FH->>NOTIF: "M-16 fallback activated"
    FH->>DASH: SSE: feed_health { state: FALLBACK_ACTIVE }

    TV->>WH: POST /webhook/observe (every 5 min)
    WH->>PB: processBar() via M-16 path
    Note over WH,PB: Trading continues uninterrupted via M-16

    Note over DB_FEED: --- DataBento reconnects ---

    FH->>DB_FEED: Reconnect attempt
    DB_FEED->>FH: Connection established
    FH->>FH: Transition: FALLBACK_ACTIVE → CONNECTED
    FH->>WH: Deactivate M-16 as primary
    FH->>BB: Resume processBar() trigger
    FH->>NOTIF: "DataBento reconnected"
    FH->>DASH: SSE: feed_health { state: CONNECTED }
